This paper deals with power allocation for localization in wireless networks, which is a problem related to networked systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). The optimization framework proposed in the paper involves mathematical programming and convex optimization, which are topics covered in machine learning (cs.MA) and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper focuses on wireless localization, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
